version_description: Capo on II. Steve plays it not exactly like that, but it sounds good. Play D7 and D#7 in the bridge like a C7-Chord moved to frets 3 and 4.

Noticed there were no versions of this song that were complete. Here are the chords all the way through and placed correctly. This song is in drop d and finger picked. For beginners I find it easiest to chord it in standard tuning 1/2 step down.
This is a simple acoustic guitar version of this song in the original key.
